Using Async/Await
useEffect(() => {

    const fetchEmployees = async () => {

        try {

            const response = await getEmployees();

            setEmployees(response.data);

        } catch(error) {

            setError("Failed to fetch data");

        } finally {

            setLoading(false);

        }
    };

    fetchEmployees();

}, []);
Interview Questions
Why use useEffect for API calls?

Because API calls are side effects and should run after component rendering.

Why use Axios instead of Fetch?
Automatic JSON parsing
Better error handling
Request/Response interceptors
Timeout support
What is response.data?

Axios wraps the HTTP response.

response.data

contains the actual API payload.
